theorem smul_apply [SMul R Y] (r : R) (f : locally_constant X Y) (x : X) : («expr • » r f) x = «expr • » r (f x) :=

one_apply:
@[to_additive]
theorem one_apply [One Y] (x : X) : (1 : locally_constant X Y) x = 1 :=
  rfl
#align one_apply one_apply
mul_apply:
@[to_additive]
theorem mul_apply [Mul Y] (f g : locally_constant X Y) (x : X) : (f * g) x = f x * g x :=
  rfl
#align mul_apply mul_apply
inv_apply:
@[to_additive]
theorem inv_apply [Inv Y] (f : locally_constant X Y) (x : X) : f⁻¹ x = (f x)⁻¹ :=
  rfl
#align inv_apply inv_apply
div_apply:
@[to_additive]
theorem div_apply [Div Y] (f g : locally_constant X Y) (x : X) : (f / g) x = f x / g x :=
  rfl
#align div_apply div_apply

coe_char_fn:
theorem coe_char_fn (hU : is_clopen U) : (char_fn Y hU : X → Y) = set.indicator U 1 :=
  rfl

char_fn_inj:
theorem char_fn_inj [nontrivial Y] (hU : is_clopen U) (hV : is_clopen V) (h : char_fn Y hU = char_fn Y hV) : U = V :=
  set.indicator_one_inj Y <| coe_inj.mpr h
#align char_fn_inj char_fn_inj
char_fn_eq_zero:
theorem char_fn_eq_zero [nontrivial Y] (x : X) (hU : is_clopen U) : char_fn Y hU x = (0 : Y) ↔ x ∉ U :=
  set.indicator_eq_zero_iff_not_mem _
#align char_fn_eq_zero char_fn_eq_zero
char_fn_eq_one:
theorem char_fn_eq_one [nontrivial Y] (x : X) (hU : is_clopen U) : char_fn Y hU x = (1 : Y) ↔ x ∈ U :=
  set.indicator_eq_one_iff_mem _
#align char_fn_eq_one char_fn_eq_one
